#  AI Test Generator (Anthropic + Playwright)

## 📌 Overview

This project is a simple tool that uses the Anthropic API to automatically generate **Playwright C# test scaffolds** from a given URL.

It combines:

* Web scraping (HTML extraction)
* AI-based test generation
* Playwright automation

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

1. User provides a URL
2. The tool fetches the page HTML
3. HTML is sent to Anthropic Claude API
4. AI generates a Playwright C# test
5. Output is printed or saved as a `.cs` file

---

## 🚀 Usage

```bash
dotnet run
```

Enter a URL when prompted:

```
https://example.com
```

---

## 🧠 Features

* Auto-generates Playwright C# test code
* Uses async/await patterns
* Supports real-world UI flows (login, forms, navigation)
* Easily extendable for Page Object Model

---

## ⚠️ Limitations

* AI-generated selectors may not always be accurate
* Requires manual validation and fixes
* Large HTML pages are truncated due to token limits

---

## 💡 Future Improvements

* Generate Page Object Model (POM) structure
* Multi-test generation (login, cart, checkout)
* CLI arguments support (`--url`, `--type`)
* GitHub Actions integration

---

## 🔑 Setup

* Add your Anthropic API key in code
* Install dependencies:

```bash
dotnet add package HtmlAgilityPack
```

---

## 🧪 Tech Stack

* C# (.NET 8)
* Playwright (test generation target)
* Anthropic Claude API

---

## 📢 Note

This project demonstrates how AI can assist in test automation, but human validation is essential for reliable and stable tests.

